Merchandise Coordinator<br>
<br>
DAVACO, Inc.<br>
<br>
Location: Albuquerque, NM<br>
<br>
*This is a part-time project based position that guarantees 4 hours, but can offer more hours.<br>
Must have footwear and apparel experience in a retail setting.<br>
<br>
Company Overview<br>
<br>
DAVACO is the North American leader in the management and execution of high-volume remodels, resets and rollouts. Founded in 1990, DAVACO currently operates headquarters in Dallas, Texas, as well as Canadian offices near Toronto. In addition, we employ over 1,000 professionals across the United States and Canada who bring extensive experience and specialized skills to deliver services to clients without disruption to their business, customers or profitability. When it comes to retail, restaurant and hospitality program management and execution, national and global brands rely on DAVACO to provide a single point-of-contact for coast-to-coast programs, customized solutions and reliable, consistent execution.<br>
<br>
If you aspire to be the best at what you do and want to be a part of a growing company, then DAVACO is the place for you. With a diverse workforce and a broad range of specialized experience and expertise, we are always looking for talented, qualified candidates to join the DAVACO team!<br>
<br>
DAVACO's Brand Merchandising Division services soft/hard line clients, ranging from fashion apparel, footwear, and accessories.<br>
<br>
Opportunity<br>
<br>
DAVACO's Brand Merchandising Division is currently seeking a vibrant merchandise coordinator with previous apparel, soft experience to support national and international brands in department, specialty, and sporting goods retailers. The ideal candidate manages product installations from inception to consumer-ready and is responsible for driving retail sales for well-known brands within major department and specialty store environments. This position is a critical, highly-visible role working with the dynamic Brand team of DAVACO.<br>
Job Description<br>
As a member of the Brand team your job will encompass different levels of responsibility that commands professionalism and confidentiality.  Below is a partial list of responsibilities.  <br>
<br>
Duties and Responsibilities<br>
<br>
&#61607;	Experience in the footwear industry is a plus.<br>
&#61607;	Primarily responsible for visual merchandising; set product to full consumer-ready state following client visual standards for merchandising.<br>
&#61607;	Soft-line merchandising expertise in a department/specialty store environment.<br>
&#61607;	Must be detail oriented, have excellent interpersonal skills, problem solving abilities, and proven leadership skills. Strong customer service skills are imperative.<br>
&#61607;	Provide Quality Control check on assigned projects and follow program reporting parameters.<br>
&#61607;	Communicate with Program Manager regarding all client concerns, challenges and opportunities on assigned projects.<br>
&#61607;	Effective time management and logical decision-making ability; ability to prioritize work, maintain a positive attitude and composure in stressful situations.<br>
&#61607;	Must be able to plan, execute and close out multiple projects or tasks in short periods of time to the satisfaction of the supervisor and/or client.<br>
&#61607;	Identifies and resolves problems in a timely manner and meets challenges with resourcefulness; ability to problem solve, with a sense of urgency and ability to prioritize.<br>
&#61607;	Partner with Field Manager to review project completion implementing best practices for application during future projects.<br>
&#61607;	Be adept at critical analysis and problem solving skills to navigate on-site hindrances to project execution.<br>
&#61607;	Prepare, submit and provide reports for each visit and submit via DAVACO's web-based portal. Clear before and after photos of completed work are required for each visit.<br>
&#61607;	Thoroughly understand project floor plans and visual merchandising guides.<br>
&#61607;	Ability to provide excellent and timely written and verbal communication.<br>
&#61607;	Dependable, with a strong work ethic.<br>
&#61607;	Consistently conduct self in professional, safe and courteous manner conducive to open retail environments in front of client and client's customers.<br>
&#61607;	Promote DAVACO services through upholding store relationships and providing pertinent feedback to the client. <br>
<br>
Required Background<br>
<br>
&#61607;	3 - 5 years of prior visual merchandising or retail management experience, preferably in a department store or specialty store environment.<br>
&#61607;	Strong interpersonal skills and extensive customer service skills.<br>
&#61607;	Ability to work independently and make sound business decisions based on client visual directives and store inventory<br>
&#61607;	Motivated/pro-active mindset in an exciting and robust work environment.<br>
&#61607;	Ability to adhere to a pre-approved monthly schedule; must be dependable with a strong work ethic.<br>
&#61607;	Strong knowledge of Microsoft Office Suite, Computers, Smart Phone, etc. and ability to use similar or equivalent technology, such as DAVACO technology, as it pertains to collecting and communicating data.<br>
&#61607;	Must have reliable transportation; must have and maintain good driving record.<br>
&#61607;	Physical ability: must be able to work on your feet for several hours at a time, lift 25 pounds, climb ladders and manipulate fixtures<br>
&#61607;	High speed internet strongly recommended.<br>
&#61607;	Adhere to company's policies, as well as compliance with federal and state legislation laws; must pass pre-employment drug screen and background check.<br>
<br>
<br>
&#8195;<br>
Disclaimer<br>
<br>
The above statements are intended to describe the general nature and level of work being performed by people assigned to this position. They are not to be construed as an exhaustive list of all responsibilities, duties, and skills required of personnel so classified. All personnel may be required to perform duties outside of their normal responsibilities from time to time, as needed.<br>
<br>
DAVACO, Inc. is an Equal Opportunity Employer and Supports a Diverse, Inclusive Work Environment<br>
<br>
All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, gender, gender identity or expression, sexual orientation, national origin, genetics, disability, age, or veteran status.<br>
<br>
Drug-Free Workplace<br>
<br>
We maintain a drug-free workplace and perform pre-employment, random, reasonable suspicion, and post-accident substance abuse testing.  We also perform pre-employment background checks.<br>
<br>
Applicants with Disabilities<br>
<br>
If you are an individual with a disability or a disabled veteran who is unable to use our online tools to search and apply for jobs, you may request a reasonable accommodation by contacting us at (214)-373-4700.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
